attributes.title: COOKING WITH YA BOY, ALEKS • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: BON APPÉTIT
attributes.description: Join your new favorite YouTube chef, ya boy, Aleks for a very special lesson in haute cuisine. Step into the mind of a master and learn this exotic interpretation of traditional polpo alla griglia. Ya boy is unveiling his prep secrets, modern updates, and what are sure to be some paradigm-shifting surprises.
attributes.display_title: COOKING WITH YA BOY, ALEKS • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: ARTISAN FAN MAIL • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: DON'T EVER GO TO ART SCHOOL
attributes.description: We got some amazing art this week from a fan who's great at metalwork, along with some of his favorite cereal. James found the pieces so inspiring that he decided to create some fine art of his own. You'll witness his foray into street art right here, along with Aleks' customary parkour warmup routine.
attributes.display_title: ARTISAN FAN MAIL • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: NINJA STARTER KIT • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: WHAT ARE THE SAFETY FEATURES OF THIS, ARE THERE ANY?
attributes.description:
Our supplier of goods of questionable legality has delivered again; we've gone from doing simple parkour to ninjutsu in just one week.
Unfortunately for us, it was the rainiest day Los Angeles had ever seen; leaving us with little to wage irregular warfare on besides the old Christmas tree.
attributes.display_title: NINJA STARTER KIT • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: ALEKS TRIES TO BECOME A CITIZEN • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: HOW HIGH IS THE UNITED STATES?
attributes.description: The time has come for Aleks to apply for naturalization, so he cracked open a Kickstart and went to work on the N-400. But is becoming a citizen as easy as it seems? This test asks Aleks the hard hitting questions he may not be prepared to answer; " Do you plan to travel outside the U.S.?" "Have you ever voted in a local election?" "Have you ever been declared legally incompetent?"
attributes.display_title: ALEKS TRIES TO BECOME A CITIZEN • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: GUYS & DOLLS • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: DO I LOOK LIKE A KOREAN POP STAR?
attributes.description: It may be no secret that we still play with toys, but dolls? Sure we play with dolls, it's 2018! Not only did we get some sweet Pit People figurines courtesy of The Behemoth,  we also played doctor with the life-size silicone doll... by giving it a skull transplant.
attributes.display_title: GUYS & DOLLS • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: SPRING CLEANING • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: DO WE HAVE SMOKE DETECTORS?
attributes.description:
Spring comes early in Southern California, which is good for us because the warehouse is like a time capsule; stuffed with junk from the past.
 We tried our hardest to decide what should stay and what should go, but some things are better left to the professionals.
attributes.display_title: SPRING CLEANING • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: MOSCOW IMPORTS  • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: I SAW ONION BUILDINGS
attributes.description: Brett and Lindsey just got back from Russia, where they attended the Warface Open Cup and drank copious amounts of водка. Upon their return, they showered Aleks with gifts from his homeland. Little did they know, a certain Cow Chop fan had also sent us a gift from his homeland, one arguably more deadly than even the strongest алкоголь.
attributes.display_title: MOSCOW IMPORTS  • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: ETERNAL RECURRENCE • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: NO RULES IN THE WEST
attributes.description: Another day, another look into what goes on behind the Cow Chop. This week our devoted fans sent in some of the craziest stuff we'd ever seen before , but not quite as crazy as what Aleks  got for us... if he can get Asher and Trevor to even look at it that is.
attributes.display_title: ETERNAL RECURRENCE • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: MAKING PLANS FOR TREVOR • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: CHICKEN ACCOMPLISHED
attributes.description:
We've been spending more quality time with Trevor recently. Before he goes on hiatus we wanted to have an all Trevor day, where we did the things he wanted to do; including: eat chicken, go thrifting, listen to music, dance, and let him drive.
We also recorded an extensive library of Trevor's reactions to various circumstances to be used in future videos and for future generations.
attributes.display_title: MAKING PLANS FOR TREVOR • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: F•R•I•E•N•D•S FOREVER • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: YOU'RE MORE LIKE A PHOEBE
attributes.description: Our dear old besties Sugar Pine 7 came over this week to show off their camera, which (apparently) still shoots RAW. They join us as we open our biggest cache of fan mail, to date, from some of our biggest fans across the world; from Italy, to Australia, to Detroit, to Dalingshan Town, Dongguan City, Guangdong Province, China!
attributes.display_title: F•R•I•E•N•D•S FOREVER • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: EXTREME SPORTING • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: NOW THAT WAS EXTREME
attributes.description: We finally got around to giving our lobby (another) extreme makeover by hanging up all the art we've been collecting. The 2nd round of Spring cleaning unearthed our collection of forgotten vehicles from our past adventures. As is our Spring equinox ritual, we took our various wheels for a spin, broke a bunch of stuff, and got hurt. To our surprise however, the most damage was done not by a sporting good, but by an underestimated kitchen condiment.
attributes.display_title: EXTREME SPORTING • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: CRIKEN CALLING • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: YOU EVER BEEN TO JAPAN?
attributes.description: This week Criken came over to the Cow Chop warehouse for the first time ever. Aleks, not only wanted to give him a proper tour of our facilities, but also decided to cook for him; even though he told us numerous times that he had already eaten. Also, check out our obligatory opening of some of your packages; if you think that the other boxes we open is stuff we don't need, you ain't seen nothing yet!
attributes.display_title: CRIKEN CALLING • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: ADULT SWING AND S*** • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: CAN WE PUT THAT IN THE LOBBY?
attributes.description: Another week, another batch of packages sent by trolling fans; and this week we've hit the mother lode. Not only did we get some items that are NSFW, but they may not be safe for us in general.  It didn't stop us from putting ourselves at great personal risk just because a camera was rolling... until the ish itself broke the camera.
attributes.display_title: ADULT SWING AND S*** • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: SPRING BREAK HIGHLIGHTS / COW CHOP COOK OFF • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: WATCH OUT LOGAN PAUL
attributes.description: We just got back from the Let's Play Spring Break, and boy are our arms sore from electric shocks; if you're not sure why, we've included some highlights straight from the beach house. Back at the office, a fan with gourmet taste sent us some imported cazzetti that Lindsey and Jakob were so eager to get into everyone's mouths that they decided to put their dishes up against one another in an impromptu pasta cock off!
attributes.display_title: SPRING BREAK HIGHLIGHTS / COW CHOP COOK OFF • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: PAX EAST WEEKEND 2018 • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: I'VE SEEN THE DEVIL
attributes.description: Cow Chop made it out to PAX East and took Beantown by storm. Asher's birthday was the social event of the season, even though it almost didn't include Asher himself. From the world's largest gummy worm to a hat commemorating the eating of poison cleaning products, you'll get to see us meet some of our most die hard fans, and go behind the velvet rope at one of PAX's most exclusive parties.
attributes.display_title: PAX EAST WEEKEND 2018 • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: STANDEE ASSASSIN • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: I JUST WANT YOU TO BE SAFE OUT THERE
attributes.description: It was only a matter of time before someone sent in the sword Brett asked for; luckily it was a iaitō and not a 真剣, but still a cause for concern for any would-be, wood-based imposters that show up at the warehouse. After the breach of security, Aleks asks the question, "how safe are we in the warehouse?" The answer may surprise you!
attributes.display_title: STANDEE ASSASSIN • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: RHYTHM ROULETTE • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: IT'S LIKE...THINGS
attributes.description: We recently got a strike from YouKnowWho... a strike as in "3 strikes, you're out."  We decided to make the best of it by broadening out horizons; what if Cow Chop did a science show? What if we made music on the channel?   What if we made our own music videos? By the end of the same day we pretty much decided we'd never try any of those things again, and you'll see why.
attributes.display_title: RHYTHM ROULETTE • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: GHOST HUNTERS • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: WHATEVER THE GHOST IS DOING IT'S FLIPPIN' OUT
attributes.description: After our cleaners told us they heard some strange noises late at night in the warehouse, we were forced to face the reality that our office may be haunted.  Luckily, James was prepared for the inconvenience of paranormal activity and had Amazon's best product designed to catch a ghost.  Fearing what we may find out, Jakob and Asher ultimately decide some things are better left unknown... but they may be too late!
attributes.display_title: GHOST HUNTERS • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: DRIFT TRIKE • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: NOW THIS IS A COOL THING
attributes.description:
Aleks wanted to get Jakob some wheels since he has been carpooling everyday; however, Jakob doesn't have a driver's license. But Aleks has the solution, it has three wheels and doesn't require any fancy license; and while it may not be street legal, it is a start.
You'll also see us finally replace our shelf with one that screams Cow Chop, and get the recently found footage of the guys stranded in the frozen tundra somewhere near the Grand Canyon.
attributes.display_title: DRIFT TRIKE • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: KENDO KLATCH • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: I ALWAYS HEAR YANNY
attributes.description: Another week, another huge stack of suspicious packages. But this time not only did we receive a sweet Luchador mask, we also received the keno sticks to go with it. We immediately began our training to become kendōkas, and we found out that it isn't hard to hit each other. We also got used Play-Doh, some sick fan art, and to the bottom of whether it's "Laurel" or "Yanny."
attributes.display_title: KENDO KLATCH • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: HOT SAUCE ORIGINAL • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: 4 FIRE ON A SCALE OF 5 FIRES
attributes.description: Ya Boy, Aleks has come through again; this time with a "Hot Sauce Making Kit." The capsaicin in the air had Aleks thinking mass production, but the left-over canned bugs had Brett thinking something else.
attributes.display_title: HOT SAUCE ORIGINAL • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: AIRSOFT FIELD TRIP • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: THIS THING WHIPS
attributes.description: With that harsh Winter behind us we've been journeying out beyond the warehouse more. In fact, Aleks just took us on a field trip to a whole different warehouse in scary/dangerous downtown LA to shoot airsoft guns. The Spring air got the best of Aleks and he may have done a drive-by on a mailbox, but the trip was a blast; no one got arrested (yet).  Then, James and Lindsey take a trip to the zoo. And because this zoo went out of business, we get a cribsesque view into the bear's old cave. Unfortunately, our visit was cut short when James realized what people had been using these cages for recently.
attributes.display_title: AIRSOFT FIELD TRIP • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: DONATING GARBAGE • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: DON'T SLIP IN THE WHISKEY
attributes.description: After James received a book on political correctness that we all so desperately needed, Aleks decided a libation was in order to celebrate our new enlightenment. Also, we had some old stuff lying around that we wanted to throw away, but it wouldn't fit in the dumpster; so, we took it down the street to the thrift store.
attributes.display_title: DONATING GARBAGE • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: MEATBALL STORE • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: I'VE BEEN TO SWEDEN BEFORE
attributes.description: Although we try to never leave the warehouse, sometimes we need things that Amazon may not have. Everyone seemed to be doing fine in the outside world until James was faced with his fear of being in a crowded space while faced with meatballs. It didn't get much better from there and we became among the rare few who get to leave Ikea the way we came in. Later on down the road however, our luck does a 180 when the next store we film inside contains a fan who rolls out the red carpet for famous screamer James.
attributes.display_title: MEATBALL STORE • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: GO SKATEBOARDING DAY  • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: WHY ARE YOU CRYING?
attributes.description: Summer has officially arrived, you can tell not only by the return of ants to our warehouse, but also this week was Go Skateboarding Day. Displacement Board Company sent us a box with our own custom Cow Chop board making us all Displacement Board Co. team riders!  Aleks, James, and Brett begin filming their new video parts immediately; and what they lack in skills on the board they make up for by using a bottle of Carolina Reaper hot sauce... switch.
attributes.display_title: GO SKATEBOARDING DAY  • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: BLOWTORCH UNBOXING • Behind The Cow Chop
attributes.caption: THAT'S A MEME I SAW IT
attributes.description: As we seek to further domesticate our production facility, Brett realized that we were missing something capable of shooting fire; 45 minutes later he had a blowtorch from some store down the street. But, does it actually work, is another story. Also, James bids good riddance to most of the office's vehicles, fans send us some stuff to hang on the wall, and Aleks decides to get into the tagging scene.
attributes.display_title: BLOWTORCH UNBOXING • Behind The Cow Chop

attributes.title: 20' TRAMPOLINE IN THE KITCHEN
attributes.caption: I'M BUILDING YOUR TRAMPOLINE
attributes.description: James felt like Cow Chop was getting too Hollywood ever since we had sets built; it had been too long since something oversized and unnecessary occupied a large amount of space in the kitchen. But fear not, because it was also James who corrected the situation and had a 20' trampoline complete with safety net and basketball hoop installed in his honor. Also check out Amazon Prime Time preparation gone wet and wild, a wedding invite from 2 fans and lovers, and a friend of ours who was called in to exterminate 100 million ants.
attributes.display_title: 20' TRAMPOLINE IN THE KITCHEN

attributes.title: ANIME BODY PILLOW
attributes.caption: TWO'S A CROWD, THREE'S A COMPANY
attributes.description: Aleks recently attended Anime Expo and became a otaku overnight. He's even brought a few "friends" back with him and has decided to introduce one to Asher; who is single, but is he ready to mingle? Asher's idea of a HOT date is bound to include more than falling asleep while watching Yuri on Ice. We also tried to class things up with our first ever wine tasting event, "try" being the key word.
attributes.display_title: ANIME BODY PILLOW

attributes.title: WATERMELON CHALLENGE
attributes.caption: I THINK I ACTUALLY CRACKED SOMETHING
attributes.description: The tropically hot July weather has Aleks exploring all Summer has to offer... via Instagram. Can Alec's thicc legs make a sweet melon bust? Is Gallagher raging uncontrollably somewhere? Will these broken melons make our ant problem exponential worse? All that plus the secret to Tony Macaroni's impeccable Van Dyke this week on Behind the Cow Chop.
attributes.display_title: WATERMELON CHALLENGE

attributes.title: ARE YOU GOING TO SAWCON?
attributes.caption: THE AFTERTASTE IS PRETTY STRONG
attributes.description: Aleks has been making the rounds this convention season, and has even been to a few non of us have heard of ( the BOFA EXPO for instance). However, the crown jewel of  this year's innovations seems to be an annoying white-noise, noise machine that Aleks awards to Brett. But Brett has a few innovations of his own to share, one to ease wrist pain, and one that traps a very popular taste in a can. Meanwhile, James was busy with his Amazon palette, and someone delivered the first offical damage to our used-to-be-new sets; can you guess who?
attributes.display_title: ARE YOU GOING TO SAWCON?

attributes.title: BUYING A $4000 FUR COAT
attributes.caption: THAT'S JUST THE WAY IT IS... SOME THINGS WILL NEVER CHANGE
attributes.description: Remember that fur coat James wore, uh the one time? Anyways we have found the behind the scenes footage of a fun little outing with the boys, shopping and picking out fun outfits. They sure do love a good thrift store that also kind of smells weird. One thing's for sure, ya can't take James shopping, because he'll buy a $4000 fur coat.
attributes.display_title: BUYING A $4000 FUR COAT

attributes.title: RTX 2018 ALL ACCESS
attributes.caption: I'M GONNA REPORT HER
attributes.description: It was a big week for everyone in the Let's Play Family, RTX Austin was the social event of the season; and naturally Cow Chop had to take the city by storm. Even if you missed it IRL, today you get a front row seat to the madness and mayhem that ensued as we make our mark on Bat City.
attributes.display_title: RTX 2018 ALL ACCESS

attributes.title: FORTNITE SHIELD POTION IRL
attributes.caption: THIS WOULD BE IS GOOD FOR YOUR HOLE
attributes.description: Aleks was awake for 3 days streaming; then on Monday, he came in dressed as Sonic the Hedgehog with an idea he was sure would work. Alec is about to find out the hard way whether Aleks' recipe for a shield potion works, is inert, or will trigger his lactose intolerance. James, luckily, got to opt out of such hazardous consumables due to 4 open wisdom tooth sockets, but someone will have to try the fan mailed hard liquor from Chicago  (which is made in Florida) and the beef jerky made out of bofa a bulls balls.
attributes.display_title: FORTNITE SHIELD POTION IRL

attributes.title: FLOOR IS LAVA CLEANUP
attributes.caption: WHAT ARE WE GOING TO DO ABOUT THE PLAYGROUND?
attributes.description:
It has been an extremely busy week at Cow Chop; the Floor is Lava challenge left the warehouse in shambles, it took days worth of mopping up whipped cream and three dumpsters full of broken swing set to get back to zero. At least there wasn't actual Lava!
We also got invited to play Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice before its release, and we got a very large box in the mail containing something you might remember.
attributes.display_title: FLOOR IS LAVA CLEANUP

attributes.title: SPONSORED BY SPYRO
attributes.caption: HOW HARD IS IT TO CLEAN UP WD-40?
attributes.description: Cow Chop kicked Labor Day weekend off with 2 promotional Spyro pool floats sent to us by Activision. But, with no pool and Summer over, will Spyro collect dust while waiting on an audition for CCTV? Not on James' watch, who noticed that the floor could be used not only as lava, but also as one big Slip 'n' Slide; just add an unhealthy amount of any brand of penetrating oil and try not to hit your face on the concrete.
attributes.display_title: SPONSORED BY SPYRO

attributes.title: BURNER PHONE
attributes.caption: WELCOME TO COW CHOP HOW CAN I HELP YOU?
attributes.description: Cow Chop has had a busy first week of Fall, complete with getting through our weekly fan-mail, tagging our graffiti wall with real spray paint indoors, and, of course, tricking Adam Kovic into drinking Malört. But, the peak of the week had to be using the cell phone our sponsor sent us to reach out to the fans... by tweeting out the number. What questions do fans like you ask Cow Chop when you got them on the line?  Highlights include, "What kind of freezer do you have?" And us showing them.
attributes.display_title: BURNER PHONE

attributes.title: BUILDING THE BATTLESHOTS
attributes.caption: THIS IS THE WRONG COLOR FOR ANYTHING
attributes.description: Cow Chop took off for London in a whirl that spun up a deadly storm of BTS footage, and left Aleks alone in the warehouse with his cow trophy. Nonetheless, watch as James fulfills a life-long dream, Aleks tags his dog (without a collar), and we take you inside the Cow Chop Weapons Lab to show how our Battleshots are made.
attributes.display_title: BUILDING THE BATTLESHOTS

attributes.title: COW CHOP GOES TO LONDON
attributes.caption: SOD OFF
attributes.description: Welcome back to Behind the Cow Chop! This week's episode features a super fun journey through London, England. Follow along as the crew checks out the Tower of London and meets tons of YOU guys. And even in England, we get kicked out of somewhere. It's just too easy. Sit back, get yourself a cuppa, and enjoy BTS.
attributes.display_title: COW CHOP GOES TO LONDON

attributes.title: EXPLOSION AFTERMATH & RUSSIAN SNACKS
attributes.caption: WHERE DA FAYGO AT?
attributes.description: Welcome back to Behind the Cow Chop! The guys got some packages, and we're checking out all the goodies. Some crappy clothes and some interesting russian snacks. Also you can catch some of the aftermath of the exploding fire extinguisher ball, and get a sneak peak to maybe some future plans for them. Also is it a fat joke? We can't tell. But meet us in the station wagon, we're going to the juggalo festival this weekend.
attributes.display_title: EXPLOSION AFTERMATH & RUSSIAN SNACKS

attributes.title: HALLOWEEN SHOPPING SPREE
attributes.caption: WHERE ARE THE FORTNITE COSTUMES?
attributes.description: Welcome back to Behind the Cow Chop! THE TIME HAS COME... October. Time to get our spoopy on and deck out the place in super spooky garb and decor. James and Lindsey hit a Halloween mega store to find some decorations.
attributes.display_title: HALLOWEEN SHOPPING SPREE

attributes.title: COKE, CANNABIS, AND MORE MORE MORE MALORT
attributes.caption: IT'S NOT GONNA MAKE YOU DRUNK.. IT IS GONNA RUIN YOUR LIFE
attributes.description: Welcome back to Behind the Cow Chop! The guys have a few special guests over and they somehow convince said guests to try the notorious Malort. Who can hang? Find out.
attributes.display_title: COKE, CANNABIS, AND MORE MORE MORE MALORT

attributes.title: HOW TO FILL A DUNK TANK WITH JELLO
attributes.caption: I GUESS WE'LL SEE IF IT BLINDS SOMEBODY...
attributes.description: Welcome back to Behind the Cow Chop! Here's your chance to get a sneak peek behind the scenes of our very special Halloween Livestream. Take a look into what goes into filling a dunk tank with jello, bobbing for apples in a tub of Malort, and how to get rid of 400 lbs of wrestling jello.
attributes.display_title: HOW TO FILL A DUNK TANK WITH JELLO

attributes.title: IT'S FINALLY HERE
attributes.caption: THANKS FoR NOT SENDING A REAL ROTTING PUMPKIN
attributes.description: Welcome back to Behind the Cow Chop! We've got a little pile of Fan mail to catch up on, and we'll also take a look into what it takes to get all dressed up for these role playing table top games we've been into. ALSO OUR ARCADE CABINET HAS FINALLY ARRIVED!!!
attributes.display_title: IT'S FINALLY HERE

attributes.title: DRIVING OVER STUFF
attributes.caption: COW CHOP MERCH CAN SURVIVE *ALMOST* ANYTHING
attributes.description: Welcome back to Behind the Cow Chop! Also, we run over stuff. Cause we're metal AF.
attributes.display_title: DRIVING OVER STUFF

attributes.title: NASAL NAPALM TASTE TEST
attributes.caption: IT'S GIVING ME A CHEMICAL BURN IN MY STomACH
attributes.description: Welcome back to Behind the Cow Chop! This week, there's quite a bit of snacks to try in our fan mail. Some is bad, but most is bad. It's all bad. Also Alec and Lindsey went on a quick Target run for some holiday preparations.
attributes.display_title: NASAL NAPALM TASTE TEST

attributes.title: BLOOPERS AND DELETED BITS
attributes.caption: CRIKEN IS HUNKY
attributes.description: Welcome back to Behind the Cow Chop! This week we're taking a deep dive into makings of our holiday specials. Costumes, costumes, props and more costumes were ordered. Also please enjoy these fun bloopers and deleted scenes. Thanks. Bye.
attributes.display_title: BLOOPERS AND DELETED BITS
